description.narrative: In 2021, UNICEF supported sub-national equity in humanitarian action, providing non-food items to youth and to organizations of persons with disabilities that mobilized to help their communities and peers in Dili municipality in response to the floods. In addition, 316;adolescents and youth (67% girls/women) in evacuation centers and affected communities accessed life-skills based education (LSBE). UNICEF also helped foster a dialogue between youth and Government officials on responding to the needs of youth in the context of COVID-19. Finally, UNICEF continued to support youth-led research project, with successful knowledge transfer to the four participating youth groups. | Status:Constrained | As-of Date:30/12/2021
